ol.li:
Run the following command and then enter the statements in cbq:
$ cbq -b=on -e
              "http://127.0.0.1:8095/" 
            cbq> create bucket beerBucket with { "bucket": "beer-sample", "nodes": "127.0.0.1" };
cbq> create shadow dataset beers on beerBucket;
cbq> connect bucket beerBucket with { "password": "" };

Send the request to the server by running the following command:
cbq> \;You must enter this special terminating sequence to execute the request. This differs from the normal cbq, which does not accept multi-line inputs.
